<taxonomicName id="4C42E5F393272014FCF9FD15CF0FFC87" authority="Shih, 2015: 154" authorityName="Shih" authorityPageNumber="154" authorityYear="2015" box="[835,1069,764,786]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Xeruca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936426293272014FCF9FD15C8AAFC87" box="[835,904,765,786]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Xeruca</emphasis>
Shih, 2015: 154
</taxonomicName>
. 
<typeStatus id="54F920D293272014FB8DFD14CF4AFC84" box="[1079,1128,764,785]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C42E5F393272014FB79FD15C8BEFCBB" authority="Rathbun, 1921" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1921" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Uca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosensis">
<emphasis id="B936426293272014FB79FD15CE47FC84" box="[1219,1381,764,786]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Uca formosensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD3E38193272014FAD1FD14C8BEFCBB" author="Rathbun MJ" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" pagination="155 - 156" refId="ref21785" refString="Rathbun MJ (1921) New species of crabs from Formosa. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 34: 155 - 156." type="journal article" year="1921">Rathbun, 1921</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation. Gender feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358CDFB93272014FCF9FCBFCFFBFABA" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFD9E7093272014FCF9FCBFC8DDFB5A" blockId="20.[835,1475,855,1231]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis id="B936426293272014FCF9FCBFC898FCFA" bold="true" box="[835,954,855,879]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Large-sized species (carapace width about 
<quantity id="4CBA339593272014FA1DFCBFC84EFC1B" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
in adults); dorsal carapace surface without posterolateral striae; front narrow; cornea round; eyestalks slender; adult male major cheliped very large; right- or left-handed, deep fingers (with straight cutting margins&gt;1/2 length of fingers), pollex without ventral carina, outer surface of major manus with moderate-szied to large tubercles, carpus with anterodorsal area flattened to facilitate chela flexion, setae on merus of minor cheliped long, thin; male pleonites free; pleonal locking mechanism absent; no setae on lateral margins of posterior stem region of urocardiac ossicles in gastric mill. 
<collectingCountry id="F355DEE093272014FCFFFB5FC8B7FB5A" box="[837,917,1207,1231]" name="Taiwan" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
endemic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD9E7093272014FCF9FB1FCF2AFA9B" blockId="20.[835,1241,1271,1327]" box="[835,1032,1271,1295]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis id="B936426293272014FCF9FB1FCF23FA9A" bold="true" box="[835,1025,1271,1295]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Species included</emphasis>
:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD9E7093272014FCF9FAF0CFFBFABA" blockId="20.[835,1241,1271,1327]" box="[835,1241,1303,1327]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">
<taxonomicName id="4C42E5F393272014FCF9FAF0CFF7FABA" authority="(Rathbun, 1921)" baseAuthorityName="Rathbun" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[835,1237,1303,1327]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Xeruca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosensis">
<emphasis id="B936426293272014FCF9FAF0CF3AFABA" box="[835,1048,1303,1327]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Xeruca formosensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD3E38193272014FB92FAFFCFEFFABA" author="Rathbun MJ" box="[1064,1229,1303,1327]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" pagination="155 - 156" refId="ref21785" refString="Rathbun MJ (1921) New species of crabs from Formosa. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 34: 155 - 156." type="journal article" year="1921">Rathbun, 1921</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358CDFB93272014FCF9FABFCEA5F8DA" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD9E7093272014FCF9FABFCEA5F8DA" blockId="20.[834,1475,1367,1871]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis id="B936426293272014FCF9FABFC890FAFA" bold="true" box="[835,946,1367,1391]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Remarks.</emphasis>
Although Rathbun described this large endemic Taiwanese species in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD3E38193272014FB92FA9FCFF3FA1A" author="Rathbun MJ" box="[1064,1233,1399,1423]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" pagination="155 - 156" refId="ref21785" refString="Rathbun MJ (1921) New species of crabs from Formosa. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 34: 155 - 156." type="journal article" year="1921">Rathbun (1921)</bibRefCitation>
, it was not well known until the work of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD3E38193272014FBBBFA7FCFE0FA3A" author="Shih HT &amp; Mok HK &amp; Chang HW &amp; Lee SC" box="[1025,1218,1431,1455]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" pagination="164 - 177" refId="ref22687" refString="Shih HT, Mok HK, Chang HW &amp; Lee SC (1999) Morphology of Uca formosensis Rathbun, 1921 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Ocypodidae), an endemic fiddler crab from Taiwan, with notes on its ecology. Zoological Studies, 38: 164 - 177." type="journal article" year="1999">Shih et al. (1999)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD3E38193272014FB77FA7FCE7EFA3A" author="Crane J" box="[1229,1372,1431,1455]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" refId="ref16259" refString="Crane J (1975) Fiddler Crabs of the World (Ocypodidae: Genus Uca). Princeton University Press, Princeton, New Jersey, xxiii + 736 pp." type="book" year="1975">Crane (1975)</bibRefCitation>
placed it with 
<taxonomicName id="4C42E5F393272014FCC6FA50CF36FA5A" baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[892,1044,1464,1487]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Uca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetragonon">
<emphasis id="B936426293272014FCC6FA50CF36FA5A" box="[892,1044,1464,1487]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">U. tetragonon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the 
<taxonomicName id="4C42E5F393272014FBCCFA50CFC1FA5A" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1142,1251,1464,1487]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Gelasimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vocans">
<emphasis id="B936426293272014FBCCFA50CFC1FA5A" box="[1142,1251,1464,1487]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">U. vocans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-complex, in 
<emphasis id="B936426293272014FCF9FA3FC89EFA7A" box="[835,956,1495,1519]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Thalassuca</emphasis>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="4C42E5F393272014FC58FA3FCF71FA7A" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1817" box="[994,1107,1495,1519]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Gelasimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936426293272014FC58FA3FCF71FA7A" box="[994,1107,1495,1519]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Gelasimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), although she had examined only a few specimens. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD3E38193272014FBB6FA1FCFF2F99A" author="Shih HT &amp; Mok HK &amp; Chang HW &amp; Lee SC" box="[1036,1232,1527,1551]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" pagination="164 - 177" refId="ref22687" refString="Shih HT, Mok HK, Chang HW &amp; Lee SC (1999) Morphology of Uca formosensis Rathbun, 1921 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Ocypodidae), an endemic fiddler crab from Taiwan, with notes on its ecology. Zoological Studies, 38: 164 - 177." type="journal article" year="1999">Shih et al. (1999)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that it was closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C42E5F393272014FC46F9FFCF6EF9BA" authorityName="Bott" authorityYear="1973" box="[1020,1100,1559,1583]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Tubuca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936426293272014FC46F9FFCF6EF9BA" box="[1020,1100,1559,1583]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Tubuca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but cautioned that more study was needed to confirm its status. Shih (2015) recently established a separate taxon 
<taxonomicName id="4C42E5F393272014FC61F9B0CF05F9FA" authorityName="Shih" authorityYear="2015" box="[987,1063,1624,1647]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Xeruca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936426293272014FC61F9B0CF05F9FA" box="[987,1063,1624,1647]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Xeruca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for this species based on morphological (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD3E38193272014FCC9F99FCF08F91A" author="Rosenberg MS" box="[883,1066,1655,1679]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" pagination="839 - 869" refId="ref22045" refString="Rosenberg MS (2001) The systematics and taxonomy of fiddler crabs: a phylogeny of the genus Uca. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 21: 839 - 869." type="journal article" year="2001">Rosenberg, 2001</bibRefCitation>
) and molecular evidence. The present work (
<figureCitation id="137982F593272014FC31F97FC8EFF93A" box="[907,973,1687,1711]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[113,148,1904,1926]" captionTargetBox="[115,1451,321,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-10@3.[111,1454,318,1891]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. A Bayesian inference (BI) tree of the family Ocypodidae and outgroups, based on the combined 28S, 16S and COI markers. The solid circle at the node means it is strongly supported by both BI (≥ 90) and ML (≥ 70); and the open circle means only one method is strongly supported. Name of species or genus quoted means it is suggested as a synonym in this study." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5355091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5355091/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) and Shih (2015) show 
<taxonomicName id="4C42E5F393272014FB60F970CE05F93A" authorityName="Shih" authorityYear="2015" box="[1242,1319,1688,1711]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Xeruca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936426293272014FB60F970CE05F93A" box="[1242,1319,1688,1711]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Xeruca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be basal to the main 
<taxonomicName id="4C42E5F393272014FC11F95FC8D9F95A" authorityName="Bott" authorityYear="1973" box="[939,1019,1719,1743]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Tubuca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936426293272014FC11F95FC8D9F95A" box="[939,1019,1719,1743]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Tubuca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade which confirms earlier relationship speculation (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD3E38193272014FC6EF93FCF41F97A" author="Crane J" box="[980,1123,1751,1775]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" refId="ref16259" refString="Crane J (1975) Fiddler Crabs of the World (Ocypodidae: Genus Uca). Princeton University Press, Princeton, New Jersey, xxiii + 736 pp." type="book" year="1975">Crane, 1975</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD3E38193272014FBC9F93FCE14F97A" author="Shih HT &amp; Mok HK &amp; Chang HW &amp; Lee SC" box="[1139,1334,1751,1775]" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" pagination="164 - 177" refId="ref22687" refString="Shih HT, Mok HK, Chang HW &amp; Lee SC (1999) Morphology of Uca formosensis Rathbun, 1921 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Ocypodidae), an endemic fiddler crab from Taiwan, with notes on its ecology. Zoological Studies, 38: 164 - 177." type="journal article" year="1999">Shih et al., 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD3E38193272014FAFFF93FC85CF89A" author="Rosenberg MS" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" pagination="839 - 869" refId="ref22045" refString="Rosenberg MS (2001) The systematics and taxonomy of fiddler crabs: a phylogeny of the genus Uca. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 21: 839 - 869." type="journal article" year="2001">Rosenberg, 2001</bibRefCitation>
). The monotypic 
<taxonomicName id="4C42E5F393272014FB86F910CFABF89A" authorityName="Shih" authorityYear="2015" box="[1084,1161,1784,1807]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Xeruca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936426293272014FB86F910CFABF89A" box="[1084,1161,1784,1807]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Xeruca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confined to 
<collectingCountry id="F355DEE093272014FA93F91FCEE0F89A" box="[1321,1474,1783,1807]" name="Taiwan Island" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Taiwan Island</collectingCountry>
and the adjacent Penghu Islands, and thus has the smallest distribution of any genus in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C42E5F393272014FB1FF8DFCE04F8DA" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[1189,1318,1847,1871]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ocypodidae</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="137982F593272014FA8CF8DFCE58F8DA" box="[1334,1402,1847,1871]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[113,148,2063,2085]" captionTargetBox="[116,1452,1198,2048]" captionTargetId="figure-65@5.[98,1464,1174,2058]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 4. The distribution of 11 genera of fiddler crabs, mainly based on Crane (1975) and the website (http://www.fiddlercrab.info/index. html; Rosenberg, 2014)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5355097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5355097/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="159">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
